\f2\b \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 1. Dual-Stream Audio Tokenizer Layer\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 The raw audio input $x(t)$ is passed into a dual-stream neural encoder inspired by the human auditory cortex and the distinction between physical sound (
\f1\i Vaikhar\uc0\u299 
\f0\i0 ) and its language-invariant cognitive core (
\f1\i Madhyam\uc0\u257 
\f0\i0 ).\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 Stream 1 (Continuous Acoustic Context Network)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Extracts prosodic patterns, fundamental frequency ($F_0$) contours, temporal pacing, emotional variance, and environmental acoustic noise. This stream does not quantize the input; it preserves a continuous, low-frame-rate latent representation $z_\{\\text\{acoustic\}\} \\in \\mathbb\{R\}^\{d \\times T\}$, serving as an ongoing context vector that maps directly to the system's focus tracking matrix.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 Stream 2 (Invariant Shabda-Token Stream)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Quantizes acoustic phonemes into discrete, speaker-independent semantic invariants using a Vector-Quantized Variational Autoencoder (VQ-VAE) or an optimized HuBERT/WavLM backbone. This outputs a stream of high-level semantic units $s_t \\in \\\{1, \\dots, V\\\}$, capturing the 
\f1\i Spho\uc0\u7789 a-inducing
\f0\i0  essence of the speech.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf2 2. The Probabilistic Transformer Core\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 An autoregressive, decoder-only transformer model initialized over both text and invariant 
\f1\i Shabda-tokens
\f0\i0 . The continuous prosodic context vector $z_\{\\text\{acoustic\}\}$ is injected into the transformer layers using a cross-attention mechanism:\
$$\\text\{Attention\}(Q, K, V) = \\text\{softmax\}\\left(\\frac\{Q K^T\}\{\\sqrt\{d_k\}\}\\right)V$$\
where the Queries ($Q$) are derived from the internal transformer states, and Keys ($K$) and Values ($V$) are conditioned on $z_\{\\text\{acoustic\}\}$. This ensures that the generation of semantic tokens is constantly steered by the continuous acoustic envelope.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf2 3. The \uc0\u346 \u257 bdabodha Parsing Engine\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 As the transformer processes the 
\f1\i Shabda-tokens
\f0\i0 , its output hidden states are intercepted by a deterministic, grammar-bound neuro-symbolic compiler: the 
\f2\b \uc0\u346 \u257 bdabodha Parser
\f0\b0 .\
Instead of generating raw text, this engine converts the probabilistic token output into a formal 
\f1\i Navya-Ny\uc0\u257 ya-Paribh\u257 \u7779 \u257 
\f0\i0  graph structure. It applies rules derived from the four components of 
\f1\i \uc0\u346 \u257 bdabodha
\f0\i0 :\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u256 k\u257 \u7749 k\u7779 \u257  (Syntactic Expectation):
\f0\b0  A parser rule that flags incomplete statements. If a verb token like "brings" (
\f1\i \uc0\u257 nayati
\f0\i0 ) appears, the system opens dependency slots for an agent (
\f1\i kart\uc0\u257 
\f0\i0 ) and an object (
\f1\i karma
\f0\i0 ).\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Yogyat\uc0\u257  (Semantic Logical Compatibility):
\f0\b0  A validation matrix that checks logical coherence. If the model generates "He irrigates the field with fire" (
\f1\i vahnin\uc0\u257  si\'f1cati
\f0\i0 ), the 
\f1\i Yogyat\uc0\u257 
\f0\i0  filter halts the output, noting that the instrument "fire" possesses an active quality incompatible with the action of "moistening/irrigating."\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Sannidhi (Proximity):
