\f2\b\fs28 \cf2 4. The Navya-Ny\uc0\u257 ya Formal Graph Layer\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 Once parsed, the statement is mapped to an internal, symbolic Knowledge Graph structured purely as a collection of 
\f1\i Prak\uc0\u257 ra-Sa\u7747 sarga-Vi\u347 e\u7779 ya
\f0\i0  relations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 Verb-Centric Ontology Construction\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 The central node of every graph entry is a 
\f2\b Process/Action
\f0\b0  node (the verbal root or 
\f1\i Dh\uc0\u257 tu
\f0\i0 ). For example, the statement "Devadatta cooks rice" is not modeled as a property of Devadatta, but as an ongoing process of 
\f1\i P\uc0\u257 ka
\f0\i0  (cooking):\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3                      [ Process: P\uc0\u257 ka (Cooking) ]\
                       /                     \\\
        (Anuk\uc0\u363 la-K\u7771 ti / Relation)       (Anuk\u363 la-Vy\u257 p\u257 ra / Relation)\
                     /                         \\\
                    v                           v\
         [ Agent: Devadatta ]            [ Object: Rice (Ta\uc0\u7751 \u7693 ula) ]\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f2\b\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
